# Topic 7 — DAG Scheduling

# What is Scheduling?

Scheduling defines:

* when a DAG runs
* how often it runs

Airflow scheduler checks DAG schedule continuously.

---

# Why Scheduling Matters

Without scheduling:

```text id="4n3x9x"
Manual Trigger Only
```

With scheduling:

```text id="n7yyi8"
Automatic Pipeline Execution
```

Example:

* daily ETL
* hourly reports
* weekly backups

---

# Schedule Parameter

Defined inside DAG:

```python id="mc2fzc"
schedule="@daily"
```

