# Important Concept — start_date

```python id="dzq1u3"
start_date=datetime(2025, 1, 1)
```

Defines:

* when scheduler starts considering DAG runs

Not actual execution time.

This confuses beginners heavily.

---

# Important Concept — catchup

## What is Catchup?

Controls whether missed DAG runs execute.

---

# Example

Suppose:

```text id="8vxy4j"
start_date = Jan 1
today = Jan 10
schedule = daily
```

Missed runs:

* Jan 1
* Jan 2
* Jan 3
  ...

---

# catchup=True

Airflow runs all missed schedules.

---

# catchup=False

Airflow runs only latest schedule.

---

# Recommended for Beginners

```python id="nl5cfz"
catchup=False
```

Otherwise:

* huge backfills
* confusing executions
* too many DAG runs

