# Full Example DAG

```python id="u1gg7r"
from airflow import DAG
from airflow.operators.python import PythonOperator
from datetime import datetime

def sample():
    print("Scheduled DAG Running")

with DAG(
    dag_id="scheduled_dag",
    start_date=datetime(2025, 1, 1),
    schedule="*/5 * * * *",
    catchup=False
) as dag:

    task1 = PythonOperator(
        task_id="sample_task",
        python_callable=sample
    )
```

---

# Scheduler Flow

```text id="z77ul9"
Scheduler Reads DAG
        ↓
Checks Schedule
        ↓
Creates DAG Run
        ↓
Tasks Execute
```

---

# Important Distinction

## DAG Definition

Static Python code.

---

## DAG Run

Actual execution instance.

Example:

```text id="dyy3s7"
daily_sales_dag
```

Can have:

* Jan 1 run
* Jan 2 run
* Jan 3 run

Same DAG definition.
Different DAG runs.

